<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>You must remove the shifter housing to lock the transmission.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage two (2) mainshaft synchronizers into two (2) mainshaft gears to lock the transmission
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i9">Figure 189</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026i9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026i9" filename="../figg13/G13026I9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 189. Engage Mainshaft Synchronizers into Mainshaft Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the speedometer drive gear rotor or replacement spacer on the output shaft inside
                the rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j0">Figure 190</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026j0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026j0" filename="../figg13/G13026J0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 190. Install Speedometer Drive Gear Rotor or Replacement Spacer and Slide Companion
                    Flange or Yoke onto Output Shaft
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the companion flange or yoke onto the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j0">Figure 190</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the output shaft nut; tighten to 300 to 350 ft-lbs. (407 to 475 N&#8226; m).</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Unlock the transmission.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
